  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bbf \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9c\u0bc2\u0bb2\u0bc8 1 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b86\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Palaly Airport operations will start from July 1",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "The government has decided to resume operations at the Palaly International Airport from July 1.",
        "Intergovernmental operations at Palaly Airport commenced on November 11, 2019, confirming basic international regulatory requirements.",
        "However, its activities were temporarily postponed until March 15, 2020 due to the Covit 19 infection.",
        "Internationally and locally established airlines have now submitted applications for charter flights and scheduled flights from the airport to the South Indian Airport.",
        "Accordingly, the Cabinet approved the proposal made by the Minister of Ports and Aviation Services to commence the international operations of the Palaly International Airport from July 1."
      ],
